<headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 21 at 3:57PM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...A period of freezing rain and sleet expected into this
evening...
Mixed precipitation has moved into the western and central Mohawk
Valley and Schoharie Valley, mainly a mix of sleet and freezing
rain. Light freezing rain and sleet will continue into this
evening. Temperatures will rise above freezing well before
midnight, changing everything to rain.
A light accumulation of freezing rain on untreated surfaces and
exposed objects can be expected. Motorists are advised to slow
down and allow extra distance between yourself and others.</description>
